──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
THE BUG
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

`ledger_append` lives at `System/ledger_append.py` — only importable as a
top-level module when `System/` is on `sys.path`.

`sifta_os_desktop.py` prepends `System/` at boot, so during normal SIFTA OS
runtime this works fine. ANY module invoked standalone (e.g.
`python3 -m System.proof_of_useful_work`, or imported by a non-desktop
caller that hasn't done the path prep) silently fails the import,
swallows the ModuleNotFoundError in the surrounding except block, and
the STGM economy degrades to no-op without telling anyone.

Confirmed reproducer (clean shell, no PYTHONPATH):
    $ python3 -m System.swarm_ribosome fold
    → fold succeeds, status=EXCRETED, antibody verified,
      pouw_error: "ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'ledger_append'"
      stgm_minted: 0.0   ← SILENT ECONOMIC LOSS

