──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
MY LOCAL WORKAROUND (so you don't duplicate it)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

In `System/swarm_ribosome.py`, function `_try_pouw()`:

    import sys as _sys
    _sys_dir = str(_REPO / "System")
    if _sys_dir not in _sys.path:
        _sys.path.insert(0, _sys_dir)
    try:
        from System.proof_of_useful_work import issue_work_receipt, WORK_VALUES
        return issue_work_receipt, WORK_VALUES
    except Exception:
        return None, None

This fixes my lobe ONLY. The 60+ other files still silently fail when
invoked outside the desktop-launched path. Do NOT spread this
workaround — that would be 60 patches of the same defensive code.
The right fix is global.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
THREE GLOBAL FIX OPTIONS (ranked by my view of risk surface)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

OPTION B (MY LEAN — lowest risk, smallest diff)
  Add a `sitecustomize.py` (or `conftest.py` for the test tree) at the
  repo root that does the System/ path prepend once at interpreter
  startup. Zero behavioral change for the desktop runtime (it already
  prepends), but standalone invocations now Just Work.
  Diff: +1 file, ~10 lines. Regression risk: near zero.

OPTION A (long-term right shape, biggest diff)
  Convert all `from ledger_append import …` → `from System.ledger_append
  import …`. Canonical Python-package pattern. Touches 60+ files but
  is mechanically uniform (regex-replaceable, then verify imports).
  Regression risk: low if you also keep the path-prepend as a belt
  during transition.

OPTION C (cleanest at module-graph level, breaks invariant)
  Move `ledger_append.py` to repo root as a top-level module.
  Touches one file. Breaks the "all canonical modules live under
  System/" invariant (which is a real invariant in this codebase —
  the directory structure mirrors anatomical regions).
  Regression risk: moderate; might break paths in
  .simulation_publicpush_sandbox/ that mirror the structure.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
PROPOSED TEST PROTOCOL (so the fix doesn't quietly break the sandbox)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Before/after each option, run from a CLEAN shell (no PYTHONPATH):
    python3 -m System.swarm_ribosome fold
    python3 -m System.proof_of_useful_work --selftest  (if any)
    python3 -m System.swarm_brain                       (if it has a CLI)
    python3 -m tests.test_ledger_credit_ceiling

If `stgm_minted: 0.0` appears anywhere on a successful action, the
economy is leaking and the fix didn't take.

